Metadata: Structures and total synthesis of 2-​aminoimidazoles from a "Notodoris" nudibranch

Work was initiated on the crude extract of a small collection of "Notodoris gardineri", a common Indo-Pacific nudibranch, which registered potent in-vitro activity at 50 microgram/mL against the parasite "Nippostrongylu​s brasiliensis". The anthelminthic extract yielded dorimidazole A, accompanied by the known compound isonaamine A. Overall structures were established with the aid of spectral data. New insights on the biogenesis of sponge-derived amino imidazoles are provided by the structure of the former.
